title: The Wall Street Journal: Online used-car seller Vroom seeks June IPO in confidential filing
text: Online used-car seller Vroom Inc. has filed confidentially for an initial public offering it hopes to stage in June, according to people familiar with its plans, a move that will test the ice-cold tech IPO market.

title: U.S. stock futures about flat coming off last week's rally
text: U.S. stock index futures were about flat late Sunday. As of 7 p.m. Eastern, Dow Jones Industrial Average futures YM00, -0.03% were down 15 points, or 0.1%, while S&P 500 futures ES00, -0.05% and Nasdaq-100 futures NQ00, -0.00% were also down fractionally.

title: 3 Bitter Truths About The Coronavirus Job Losses And The Economy

title: Oil prices fall 1% as glut weighs
text: Oil prices opened about 1% lower on Sunday as a persistent glut continued to weigh on prices and the coronavirus pandemic eroded global oil demand even as some governments began to ease  lockdowns.

title: Temporary Unemployment Spike Brings Silver Lining To Terrible Jobs Data
text: April's unemployment number is unprecedented, but a spike in temporary unemployment could hint at a V-shaped recovery.

title: US stock futures fall following back-to-back rallies
text: U.S. stock futures fell on Sunday night after Wall Street posted consecutive rallies to end last week amid the prospects of the global economy reopening soon.

title: US is risking a second coronavirus wave and a depression, economist Mark Zandi warns
text: Mark Zandi of Moody's Analytics' worries businesses may reopen too soon and create another spike in coronavirus cases.

title: How Bill Ackman Sources New Investment Ideas

title: Investors Disconnect?
text: Despite some negative economic data, the bear market rally continues. This week, the Viper Report's Tom examines the disconnect between the data and market behavior, and looks at some similar disconnects from past bear markets.

title: Mnuchin says jobless numbers will 'get worse before they get better' — unemployment may have hit 25%

title: One Chart to Explain the Importance of Staying Invested
text: By Eric Dutram, Contributor, DWS Market volatility has been soaring as of late thanks to the unprecedented uncertainty surrounding COVID-19. As is generally the case in these types of volatile market environments, investors may be thinking about pulling away from equities and waiting for events to settle down.

title: Markets look vulnerable as countries ease lockdowns
text: So far, most investors have viewed the easing of lockdown measures as a big positive for markets.

title: Unemployment benefits should be tied to unemployment rate: Senator  Wyden
text: Oregon Senator Ron Wyden wants to tie expanded unemployment insurance to state unemployment rates during the COVID-19 pandemic.

title: Trump Officials Say Unemployment Could Hit 25%, But No New Stimulus Coming Soon
text: The U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics reported that the unemployment rate soared to 14.7% in April.

title: Kudlow says White House holding informal talks with lawmakers on next steps in coronavirus relief
text: Lawmakers have passed four major relief packages to address the damage from the coronavirus as the unemployment level surged to levels unseen since the Great Depression and many businesses remain shuttered.

title: U.S. unemployment rate will get worse, Treasury's Mnuchin says
text: The staggering U.S. unemployment rate reported by the government on Friday amid coronavirus lockdowns may get even worse, Treasury Secretary Steven Mnuchin said on Sunday.

title: Unemployment hits 14.7%
text: Unemployment rate in the U.S. hit a record high of 14.7% in April. Yahoo Finance’s Jessica Smith breaks down the latest jobless claims.

text: Hiring across the U.S. saw an unprecedented drop in April over the spread of COVID-19. Yahoo Finance’s Brian Cheung joins the On The Move panel to discuss.
